<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Yotsuya_Kaidan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<dl>
<dd>
<ol>
<li><cite id="endnote_iemon" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_iemon" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Iemon is sometimes <a href="/wiki/Romanization_of_Japanese" title="Romanization of Japanese">romanized</a> as <i>Iyemon</i>, due to the kana ゑ which is no longer in use. This romanization gives a more <a href="/wiki/Archaism" title="Archaism">archaic</a> feel to the name.</li>
<li><cite id="endnote_yotsuya" style="font-style: normal;"><a href="#ref_yotsuya" title=""><b>^</b></a></cite>&#160; Yotsuya is an area of <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo's</a> Chiyoda Ward on the western edge of <a href="/wiki/Shinjuku" title="Shinjuku" class="mw-redirect">Shinjuku</a>.</li>
</ol>
</dd>
</dl>
